# Defense in depth for the uploads tree (covers project-requests/ and
# client-files/ too, since .htaccess directives inherit downward): uploads
# are already validated by extension + magic bytes at upload time, but if
# that were ever bypassed, nothing in here may execute as a script. Deny
# serves every script-ish extension outright rather than php_flag engine
# off, which only works under mod_php and 500s under FPM/LiteSpeed.
<FilesMatch "(?i)\.(php|phar|phtml|php[0-9]|pht|pl|py|cgi|sh|asp|aspx|jsp)$">
  Require all denied
</FilesMatch>

# No directory listings, ever.
Options -Indexes
